Determine the values of `x` and `y` after the following code executes:

```java
int x = 5;
int y = 10;
if (x > y)
{
    x = x * 2;
}
else
{
    y = y - x;
}
```

Which of the following correctly describes the behavior of the code below?

```java
int temp = 75;
if (temp >= 80)
    System.out.println("hot");
    System.out.println("wear sunscreen");
else
    System.out.println("cool");
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
int a = 8;
int b = 5;
if (a > b)
{
    if (a % 2 == 0)
    {
        System.out.print("even winner");
    }
    else
    {
        System.out.print("odd winner");
    }
}
else
{
    System.out.print("b wins");
}
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
int x = 15;
if (x > 10)
    if (x > 20)
        System.out.print("large");
    else
        System.out.print("medium");
System.out.print(" done");
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
int x = 0;
if (x != 0 && 10 / x > 2)
{
    System.out.print("yes");
}
else
{
    System.out.print("no");
}
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
int score = 79;
String grade;
if (score >= 90)
{
    grade = "A";
}
else if (score >= 80)
{
    grade = "B";
}
else if (score >= 70)
{
    grade = "C";
}
else
{
    grade = "F";
}
System.out.print(grade);
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
int n = 6;
boolean result = true;
if (n % 2 == 0)
{
    result = false;
}
if (n % 3 == 0)
{
    result = true;
}
System.out.print(result);
```

A programmer intends for `System.out.println("nonzero")` to execute only when `x > 0`. Which of the following correctly describes the actual behavior of the code?

```java
int x = 3;
if (x > 0)
    System.out.println("positive");
    System.out.println("nonzero");
System.out.println("done");
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
int p = 4;
int q = 8;
if (p * 2 == q)
{
    p = p + 1;
    q = q - 1;
    if (p > q)
    {
        System.out.print("X");
    }
    else
    {
        System.out.print("Y");
    }
}
else
{
    System.out.print("Z");
}
System.out.print(p + q);
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
String s1 = "hello";
String s2 = new String("hello");
if (s1 == s2)
{
    System.out.print("same ref");
}
else
{
    System.out.print("diff ref");
}
if (s1.equals(s2))
{
    System.out.print(" same val");
}
else
{
    System.out.print(" diff val");
}
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
int n = 18;
if (n % 3 == 0) {
    System.out.println("fizz");
} else {
    System.out.println("buzz");
}
```

Determine the values of `p` and `q` after the following code runs.

```java
int p = 8;
int q = 4;
if (p > q) {
    p = p - q;
} else {
    p = p + q;
}
if (p == q) {
    q = 0;
}
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
int x = 2;
if (x > 3)
    System.out.println("greater");
    System.out.println("done");
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
int a = 4;
int b = 4;
if (a == b) {
    a = a * 2;
    if (a > b) {
        b = b + 3;
    } else {
        b = b - 3;
    }
} else {
    a = 0;
    b = 0;
}
System.out.println(a + " " + b);
```

What is printed when the following code is executed?

```java
int n = 12;
String msg;

if (n % 5 == 0)
{
    msg = "fizz";
}
else
{
    msg = "buzz";
}

if (n % 4 == 0)
{
    msg = msg + "!";
}

System.out.println(msg);
```

Determine the values of `p` and `q` after the following code runs.

```java
int p = 4;
int q = 4;

if (p != q)
{
    p = p + q;
}
else
{
    q = p + q;
}
```

What is printed when the following code is executed?

```java
int val = 3;
if (val > 5)
    System.out.println("greater");
    System.out.println("done");
```

What is printed when the following code is executed?

```java
int x = 0;
int y = 10;

if (x != 0 && y / x > 2)
{
    System.out.println("safe");
}
else
{
    System.out.println("guarded");
}
```

Determine the output of the following code segment:

```java
int x = 4;
int y = 7;

if (x > 5)
    if (y > 5)
        System.out.print("A");
    else
        System.out.print("B");

System.out.print("C");
```

Determine the value of `result` after the following code segment runs.

```java
int n = 18;
String result = "";

if (n % 2 == 0)
{
    result += "E";
}
else
{
    result += "O";
}

if (n % 3 == 0)
{
    result += "T";
}
else
{
    result += "N";
}

if (n % 5 == 0)
{
    result += "F";
}
else
{
    result += "R";
}
```
